cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with language modelling and dropout techniques for neural language models. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes extensions to existing dropout techniques and evaluates their performance on language modelling tasks. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with improving the performance of neural language models, which is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper deals with neural language models and their training techniques. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with computer vision, but it does use neural networks which are commonly used in computer vision tasks.
